{
  "texts": [
    "In each block, edge, node, and graph-level features are updated synchronously and are connected through DCNs respectively, achieving a comprehensive optimization of the local chemical environment of the atoms.",
    "A more detailed explanation of the edge-node-graph update can be found in the Fig. 3.",
    "In the third block of the Fig. 1, we designed an independent readout module that aggregates node, edge, and graph features into graph-level features and inputs them into a single-layer MLP with a linear activation function to generate the final predictions of crystal properties.",
    "Throughout the hidden representations of the GNN, we uniformly used a 128dimensional feature space.",
    "Unless specified otherwise, we used the common swish activation function in the MLPs."
  ]
}